cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving object detection accuracy through a novel bounding box regression loss. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) tasks and proposes a new method for learning bounding box transformation and localization variance together. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new loss function, which is a machine learning (ML) technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for merging neighboring bounding boxes during non-maximum suppression (NMS), which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning (DL) techniques, which fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on a large-scale object detection dataset, which is a multimedia (MM) application, making cs.MM another possible sub-category.
